-- Dunkin’ Brands CEO Nigel Travis Named Chairman as Luther Retires
-- B y   D a v i d   R i s s e r
-- 2013-05-10T10:12:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-10/dunkin-brands-ceo-nigel-travis-named-chairman-as-luther-retires.html
Dunkin’ Brands Group Inc. (DNKN) , the owner
of Dunkin’ Donuts and Baskin-Robbins ice cream, said Chief
Executive Officer Nigel Travis will add the role of chairman to
succeed Jon Luther, who is retiring.  Luther, 69, will leave his posts as director and chairman
as of May 15, the Canton, Massachusetts-based company said today
in a statement.  Travis, 63, formerly of Papa John’s International Inc.,
started as Dunkin’ Brands CEO in January 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Risser in London at 
 drisser@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
